## 6. Model Comparison Summary

```{r comparison}
comparison <- data.frame(
  Model = c(
    "Full Model",
    "Stepwise (AIC)",
    "Critic × Genre Interaction",
    "Critic × User Score Interaction",
    "Polynomial Year",
    "Best Combined Model"
  ),
  AIC = round(c(
    AIC(full_model),
    AIC(step_model),
    AIC(model_int_genre),
    AIC(model_int_scores),
    AIC(model_poly_year),
    AIC(model_best)
  ), 2),
  CV_RMSE = round(c(
    mean(rmse_folds),
    mean(rmse_step),
    mean(rmse_int_genre),
    mean(rmse_int_scores),
    mean(rmse_poly_year),
    mean(rmse_best)
  ), 4)
)

kable(comparison, caption = "Model Comparison — AIC and 10-Fold CV RMSE")
```

> **Lower AIC and lower CV RMSE = better model.**
> The best model is the one with the lowest CV RMSE since that reflects out-of-sample predictive performance.


